accessibility.text: Requiring (or paying) farmers to take land out of production. This \"set-aside\" approach rarely is very effective at supporting agricultural prices.
Requiring (or paying) farmers to take land out of production. This \"set-aside\" approach rarely is very effective at supporting agricultural prices.
Farmers are profit maximizers: they set aside their least productive land first.
Furthermore, a policy that creates artificial scarcity of land induces farmers to intensify their production practices on each acre that remains in production, increasing supply.
